Running the Chatbot on IBM Cloud
To deploy and run the College Inquiry Chatbot on IBM Cloud, follow these steps:

Prerequisites
IBM Cloud Account: Make sure you have an active IBM Cloud account. If you don't have one, you can sign up here.

IBM Watson Assistant Service: Create an instance of the IBM Watson Assistant service on IBM Cloud. You can do this by following these steps:

Log in to your IBM Cloud account.
Click on "Create Resource" and search for "Watson Assistant."
Select the Watson Assistant service and follow the prompts to create an instance.
Deployment Steps
Clone the Repository:

Clone this GitHub repository to your local machine using git clone.
Configure IBM Watson Assistant:

Open the IBM Watson Assistant instance you created in your IBM Cloud account.
Import the provided dialog, intents, and entities from the bot_queries.json file located in this repository.
Customize and extend the components as needed to match your chatbot's capabilities.
IBM Cloud CLI Installation (Optional):

Install the IBM Cloud Command Line Interface (CLI) on your local machine. You can find installation instructions here.
Push to IBM Cloud:

Open a terminal window and navigate to the cloned repository directory.
Log in to IBM Cloud using the CLI:
Copy code
ibmcloud login
Target the desired IBM Cloud region (if not already set):
php
Copy code
ibmcloud target -r <region>
Push your chatbot to IBM Cloud using the following command:
perl
Copy code
ibmcloud cf push <app-name>
Replace <app-name> with a unique name for your application.
Access the Chatbot:

Once the deployment is complete, you will receive a URL where your chatbot is hosted on IBM Cloud.
Open a web browser and navigate to the provided URL to interact with your College Inquiry Chatbot.
Usage and Support
Interact with the chatbot using natural language queries related to VIT Vellore college mess inquiries.
For any questions, suggestions, or technical support, please reach out to Your Name or visit GitHub Profile.
